<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-02-0626 </DOCNO><TEXT>Prior to discussing the fundamental principles of pilot operated regulators,the author defines a pressure regulator. A pressure regulator is an automaticdevice which controls the media flow and maintains a desired media pressurewhile reducing the media supply pressure. The author discusses the pressurestandard for control of the restrictive element. The pressure standardactually results from usage of two (or more) self-operated regulatorsin combination with one being the operator and the other being the director.The operating regulator receives its orders from the directing regulatorand provides media control as directed.</TEXT></DOC>